{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566844","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566844"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:48+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:49:48+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18896"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18896","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18896"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.02,0.03,0.06,0.85]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11629"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80092"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11629"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18896"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65369"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11336"},{"type":"tags","id":"11337"},{"type":"tags","id":"11341"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27359"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27360"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80092","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80092"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA medical student observes a senior registrar repeatedly making derogatory comments about a junior doctor\u0027s clinical skills during ward rounds. The junior doctor appears distressed by these public criticisms. The medical student has documented specific examples of the behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate initial action for the medical student to take?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Wait for the junior doctor to make a complaint","Directly confront the senior registrar","Discuss concerns with other medical students first","Report to the hospital medical board","Report to the clinical supervisor or term coordinator"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate initial action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Ereport to the clinical supervisor or term coordinator\u003C/strong\u003E. This follows proper institutional channels and ensures the concern is raised with someone who has the authority to address the situation. The medical student has appropriately documented specific examples, which helps establish a clear pattern of behaviour.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWait for the junior doctor to make a complaint\u003C/strong\u003E - Witnesses to bullying have a responsibility to report it, regardless of whether the target makes a complaint\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDirectly confront the senior registrar\u003C/strong\u003E - This could escalate the situation and put the medical student at risk, given the power differential\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDiscuss concerns with other medical students first\u003C/strong\u003E - While seeking peer support is understandable, this delays appropriate action and may lead to gossip\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport to the hospital medical board\u003C/strong\u003E - This bypasses the appropriate chain of command. Local issues should first be addressed at the department level\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAll healthcare workers have a professional responsibility to contribute to a safe and respectful workplace culture. Reporting bullying through appropriate channels is essential for maintaining professional standards and protecting colleague wellbeing.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Healthcare workers have a professional obligation to report bullying and harassment when witnessed.","Reporting should follow established institutional pathways starting with direct supervisors unless they are involved.","Documentation of incidents should be contemporaneous, objective, and factual."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx","Medical Deans Australia and New Zealand. Preventing \u0026 Managing Bullying, Discrimination \u0026 Harassment A Guide for Medical Schools. [online]. April 2024 [Cited 2025 Jan 17]. Available at: https://medicaldeans.org.au/md/2024/05/Preventing-and-Managing-BDH-a-guide-for-medical-schools.pdf"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65369"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18896"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65369","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65369"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T12:42:20+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T12:43:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11629"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80092"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696